article.headline: Murray State 76, SE Missouri State 63
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Chris Shumate scored 14 points as Murray State beat Southeast Missouri 76-63 Thursday night. Shawn Witherspoon added 13 for the Racers (24-5, 13-2 Ohio Valley Conference), and Kelvin Brown scored 11. Cuthbert Victor had nine points and 15 rebounds. Reggie Golson scored 19 for Southeast Missouri (11-15, 4-11), and Derek Winans had 15. Murray led 39-23 at the half and pulled out to a 27-point advantage, 62-35, after Witherspoon hit a 3-pointer with 11:27 left in the game. The Indians closed to within 15 points, 66-51, when Golson hit a jumper with 5:55 to go. The Racers then pulled away to a 74-53 lead on a layup by Brown. Murray State was 29-of-66 (43.9 percent) from the field, while holding Southeast Missouri to 23-of-60 shooting (38.3 percent). Murray also outrebounded Southeast Missouri 47-29.
